NOTES: District is subject to "special revitalization programs and tax credits" but does not affect use.
Areas are those areas served by the Town of Fairlee municipal water system. Minimum area of a lot serviced by municipal water supply is 20,000 square feet and is classified as a Class A lot.
All new structures are prohibited in this protection area.

As delineated as an overlay district on the Zoning Map, otherwise qualified Class B lots (served my on-lot water and sewage) may be waived down to 1-acre minimum lot sizes with the transfer of subdivision rights.
